release 10.0409.17

   Video recording only base on camera triggering setting, event marker setting on a sensor do not trigger recording. Event marker only to mark a video file as LOCKED file if that channel (camera) is currently recording.

   Unsolved memeory leak to trigger system reboot through "ioprocess", run "/bin/reboot" could failed when memory is low.

   Add g-force sensor value on OSD. (not been verified)

   For TVS, OSD display selectable on camera setup page
   TVS, send sensor5 inverted state to MCU on ioprocess startup

release 10.0412.18

  TVS, send sensor2 inverted state (not sensor5) to MCU on ioprocess startup.
  eaglehttpd, add Etag and Last-Modified support.

release 10.0412.18 (tvs)
  Start recording (as locked file) when system startup.

release 10.0426.18 (pwii)
  One line overlay msg for io. Currently display "Detecting Smart Server", "Uploading Video to Smart Server", "Copying Video Files". Message set from ioprocess or other process.
  Up to 1 minute time after shutdown delay timeout to detect smart server availablity.
  If smart server detected, run "smartftp".
  If no smart server detected, go to standby mode. On standby mode, CDC is been turn off.
  Standby setting time include smartftp uploading time and standby time. After standby timeout, power off system
  Fixed lost audio when play back Front Camera
  Extend HD (CF card) mounting time to 120 seconds. (CF mounting may be up to 100s if it is not umount properly. This may cause system rebooting on previous firmware).


